    <section>
        <h>uses</h>
        <section id="uses-questions">
            <h>complement</h>
            <p>The relative particle can be used as the complement of one of the following question
                words – <ul>
                    <li><g><a href="?gd=dee">dé</a> a ... ?</g>
                        <en>what ... ?</en></li>
                    <li><g><a href="?gd=coo">có</a> a ... ?</g>
                        <en>who ... ?</en></li>
                    <li><g><a href="?gd=ciamar">ciamar</a> a ... ?</g>
                        <en>how ... ?</en></li>
                    <li><g>cuin a ... ?</g>
                        <en>when ... ?</en></li>
                    <li><g>carson a ... ?</g>
                        <en>why ... ?</en></li>
                </ul>
            </p>
            <p>Note however that the question word <g><a href="?gd=caait">càit</a> ... ?</g> <en>where ... ?</en> governs the interrogative verbal particle <a href="?gd=an^particle"><g>an</g></a> rather than the relative particle <g>a</g>.</p>
        </section>
    </section>











